Kirinyaga governor Anne Waiguru could not testify as a prosecution witness in the 791 million shillings NYS case against former principal secretary Peter Mangiti and former NYS director-general Nelson Githinji. The case was adjourned due to a lack of representation for two accused persons following the death of their lawyer. Chief magistrate Francis Andayi allowed the two ..time to get new advocates to represent them. The hearing will resume on the 5th of august.